Now enemies experience that "time slowing" horror


OPTION 2: "PHANTOM STRIKE"
What It Does:

Haruto's attacks phase through defenses
Punch goes through guard/block, hits anyway
Not intangible—just ignores barriers
Only works on living targets (can't phase through walls)

Combat Use:

Perfect offense (can't be blocked)
Forces enemies to dodge (no defense works)
Makes him unpredictable

Symbolism:

Shiori's screams went "through" walls but nobody helped
Her pain ignored all barriers
Now Haruto's attacks do the same


OPTION 3: "PRESSURE POINT"
What It Does:

Haruto can see weak points on anything (structural, physical, emotional)
Visual: Glowing marks appear on enemies (only he sees them)
Hitting marked spot = devastating effect (bones break, organs rupture, mind cracks)

Combat Use:

Surgical precision (one-hit finishers possible)
Works on objects too (shatter walls, weapons)
Requires accuracy (skill-based, not just power)

Symbolism:

Shiori was targeted at her most vulnerable
Now Haruto targets vulnerability itself


OPTION 4: "ECHO COUNTER"
What It Does:

When Haruto is attacked, he can "replay" the attack back
Absorbs hit, stores it briefly (3 seconds)
Releases it back at attacker (same force/damage)

Combat Use:

Defensive offense (tanks hit, counters immediately)
Stronger enemy attacks = stronger counters
Risk: Must time it right or takes full damage

Symbolism:

Violence done to Shiori now returns to perpetrators
"What you give comes back"


MY PICK: OPTION 2 (PHANTOM STRIKE)
Why:

Simplest mechanically (attacks ignore blocks)
Visually clear (punch phases through guard)
Terrifying in combat (no defense works)
Forces enemies to RUN not FIGHT (psychological advantage)
Fits theme (ignored barriers = Shiori's pain ignored)

Complete Power Set:

Dash Impact (speed + delayed shockwave)
Phantom Strike (attacks phase through defenses)
Emotional Transfer (touch = victim feels Shiori's death)

Three powers. Simple. Devastating.
