If a reader asks: "What's the difference?"
THE SIMPLE ANSWER:
VESTIGES = Born from human suffering

When someone experiences massive trauma caused by society's failure
Their pain becomes so intense it takes physical form
Personal, intimate, tied to specific human experience
Think: "Humanity's sins made manifest"

REMNANTS = Born from reality breaking

When the Rift (tears in reality) creates entities from pure chaos
Alien, incomprehensible, not human-origin
Primal forces, cosmic horror
Think: "The universe rejecting humanity"


THE CORE DIFFERENCE:
AspectVESTIGEREMNANTOriginHuman traumaReality fractureEmotionSpecific, personalAbstract, primalBondHuman choosesRemnant choosesGoalTied to human's purposeAlien/unknowableExampleShiori (born from Haruto's grief)Koyoi's entity (born from Rift exposure)

