She's wearing what she wore on their first date (not trip outfit yet)
Feels ring in pocket

He approaches:

She turns
Looks exactly as she did alive
But: Eyes slightly off (pale, glowing faintly)
No shadow cast

The Conversation (PHILOSOPHY HEAVY):
Haruto: "...Am I dead?"
Shiori: "No. Not yet."
Haruto: "Then what is this?"
Shiori: "A moment between moments. Before you decide."
Haruto: "Decide what?"
Shiori: "Whether to let go or hold on."
[Silence. He stares at her.]
Haruto: "They killed you. They framed it. Your parents— they—"
Shiori: "I know."
Haruto: "You know?"
Shiori: "I knew the whole time. I know everything now. What they did. What they said. How long it lasted. How nobody came."
[Her voice is flat. Not emotional—just factual.]
Haruto: "I'm going to kill them."
Shiori: "You already decided that."
Haruto: "I failed. They almost killed me."
Shiori: "Almost. But I pulled you here first."
Haruto: "Why?"
Shiori: "Because you're the only one who cares. The only one who even tried."
[Pause. He's crying. She's not.]
Haruto: "I can't bring you back."
Shiori: "No. But you can make them understand."
Haruto: "Understand what?"
Shiori: "What it feels like. To be me. To die like I did."
[She steps closer.]
Shiori: "You've always believed humanity needs to feel real pain to change. Now you can make them."
Haruto: "How?"
Shiori: "I'm not gone, Haruto. Not completely. I'm here. In this place. In you. Waiting."
Haruto: "What are you?"
Shiori: "I don't know what people would call this. But I know what I am. I'm what happens when someone dies screaming and the person who loved them refuses to let go."
[She looks at her hands.]
Shiori: "I'm neither alive nor dead. I'm what remains. And I'm tied to you now."
Haruto: "Because I won't let go?"
Shiori: "Because we won't let go. Neither of us."
The Ring Moment:
Shiori: (notices ring in his hand) "You were going to propose. At the lake."
Haruto: "I still want to."
Shiori: "I know."
Haruto: "But I can't. Not now. Not like this."
Shiori: "Why not?"
Haruto: "Because you're not—because this isn't—"
Shiori: "Because I'm dead?"
[He can't answer.]
Shiori: "Keep the ring, Haruto. And when this is over—when they've paid—go to the lake. I'll meet you there. And you can ask me properly."
Haruto: "Promise?"
Shiori: "Promise."
[She places hand on his chest. He feels cold spreading.]
Shiori: "Now go back. And show them what I felt."

RETURN TO REALITY:

Haruto wakes at assault site
Alive, healed (scars remain)
Shiori's voice in his mind: "I'm here. Always."
Stands, sees perpetrators gone (think he's dead, left)
Transformation flickers (her silhouette around his arms briefly)
Realizes: "I'm not human anymore."


