FRAGMENT 詩 - CHAPTER BREAKDOWN
~25-30 PAGES TOTAL

CHAPTER 1: THE JUDGMENT (4-5 pages)
PRESENT DAY - 2 MONTHS AFTER BOND

OPENING SCENE - ALLEYWAY, AFTERNOON
Two perpetrators cornered.
Haruto approaches slowly.
Perpetrator 1: "Look, we don't want trouble—"
Haruto stops. Silent.
Perpetrator 2: "Who the hell are you?"

THE GESTURE:
Haruto raises both hands.
Covers both eyes completely.
Stands still.
His voice shifts—not his anymore. Hers:

Shiori (through Haruto):
"You. Left side. You held me down while the others did it."
Perpetrator 1: (freezes) "What—"
"You. Right side. You laughed when I begged. Said it was just a joke."
Perpetrator 2: (voice shaking) "Who told you—"
"Nobody told me. I was there. I remember."

Haruto lowers hands.
Eyes now different:

Pale silver-gold (glowing faintly)
Not his color anymore

His own voice returns (cold):
Haruto: "She remembers everything."

THE ABILITY - TIME DILATION:
Perpetrator 2 lunges with knife.
Haruto's perception:

World slows (not stops—just crawls)
2-second window
Sees attack trajectory clearly
Steps aside (knife passes in slow motion)

Real-time:

Haruto sidesteps instantly (too fast)
Grabs Perpetrator 2's wrist
Twists (snap—bone breaks)
Elbow to face (nose shatters)
All in 2 seconds

Perpetrator 2 collapses.

Perpetrator 1 tries to run.
Time dilation activates again:

Haruto sees escape route
Dash Impact (pure speed)
Appears in front of Perpetrator 1
Punch (no phasing—just impact)
Victim flies back into wall


AFTERMATH:
Both on ground. Broken. Conscious.
Haruto kneels beside Perpetrator 1.
Touches forehead.
Haruto: "Now feel it."
Emotional Transfer activates.

Victim experiences Shiori's death (3 seconds compressed):

Terror
Pain
Betrayal
Loneliness
The moment she realized nobody was coming

Perpetrator 1 screams. Collapses. Sobbing.

Haruto stands.
Eyes fade back to normal.
Looks at his hands.
Shiori (internal): "Six more."
Haruto: "I know."
Walks away.

TRANSITION:
Internal monologue:

"Two months ago, I was dying in an alley like this."
"Now I'm the one who delivers death."
"This is how it started."

FLASHBACK.

CHAPTER 2: BEFORE (6-7 pages)
6 MONTHS EARLIER

