"We've stopped feeling. We just consume."
"Tragedy becomes content. Pain becomes entertainment."
"Social media killed empathy. We perform caring instead of doing it."

His belief:

"Humanity can be fixed. But only through forced understanding."
"People don't change until they're made to feel real consequences."


RELATIONSHIP WITH SHIORI (Already Ongoing)
Scene: Café, afternoon
They've been together 1 year.
Conversation:
Shiori: "Do you think people can actually change?"
Haruto: "Only when forced. Comfort breeds complacency."
Shiori: "So suffering is necessary?"
Haruto: "Not suffering. Understanding. If perpetrators felt what victims feel, they'd stop."
Shiori: "Empathy through experience."
Haruto: "Exactly."
[Pause. She looks at him carefully.]
Shiori: "What if they don't change? What if they feel it and still don't care?"
Haruto: "Then they're beyond saving."
Shiori: "And humanity?"
Haruto: "If enough people are beyond saving... then humanity deserves what's coming."
[She smiles slightly—not happy, just recognition.]
Shiori: "You're darker than you pretend."
