"How are you doing this?" (locations shifting)
"Why do your clothes keep changing?"
"AM I DEAD?"

Shiori explains calmly (contrast to his panic).

CHAPTER 6 - POWER EXPLANATION:
NO ability names (not "Dash Impact" etc.)
Shiori explains mechanics:
Shiori: "You're faster now. Because I exist outside time. When you move with me, reality bends."
Haruto: "How?"
Shiori: "Your punches go through things because I'm neither solid nor not. You exist in both states."
Haruto: "What about the—the slowing down thing—"
Shiori: "That's you. Your mind processing faster than your body should. Two seconds of clarity. Use it."
How it's different from others:
Shiori: "Most people bonded like us? They fight against their other half. You're listening to me. That's why it works."

KILLS - DIFFERENT METHODS:
Target 3: Drowned (held underwater in bathtub, Phantom Strike through struggle)
Target 4: Crushed (Dash Impact into wall, repeated, bones shatter)
Target 5: Burned (trapped in car, doesn't use powers—just locks door, walks away)
Each death = different, creative, personal.

PROPOSAL - REWRITTEN:
NO glowing, NO light, NO dissolving.
WHAT HAPPENS INSTEAD:
Haruto kneels.
Haruto: "I don't know what we are anymore. I don't know if this counts as living. But I know one thing."
[Pulls out ring]
Haruto: "When I thought I was dying, I didn't think about my parents. Or my sibling. Or revenge. I thought about never getting to ask you this."
[Voice breaking]
Haruto: "So I'm asking now. Even if it's too late. Even if we're both—whatever we are—"
Haruto: "Shiori. Will you marry me?"
[Silence. Wind. Water lapping.]
Shiori: (tears falling—can Vestiges cry? Yes) "You know I can't leave you now. I'm trapped. You're trapped. We're—"
Haruto: "I know."
Shiori: "This isn't fair to you."
Haruto: "Nothing's fair. I stopped caring about fair two months ago."
Shiori: "...Yes. I'll marry you."
[He slides ring onto her finger.]
THE BOND SEALS (NOT LIGHT):

Ring tightens slightly (physical sensation)
Her form becomes more solid (not less)
Temperature drops (cold spreads through both)
She takes sharp breath (didn't need to breathe before, does now)
Her hand in his feels real (was translucent, now tangible)

What this means:

Full bond = she's more anchored to reality through him
Not dissolving INTO him
Existing BESIDE him, but tethered

After:
Shiori looks at ring on her finger.
Shiori: "It's real."
Haruto: "You're real."
Shiori: "No. We're something else. But we're together."
[They stand at water's edge]
Haruto: "What now?"
Shiori: "Now we live. However long we have."
Haruto: "And when it's over?"
Shiori: "Then at least we'll go together."

FINAL IMAGE:
They walk away from lake together.
Her hand in his (solid, cold, real).
Two figures. Two shadows.
Lake behind them reflects Mt. Fuji.
Empty.
Still.

COMPLETE REVISION SUMMARY:
✅ Opening: Perpetrator 1 fleeing (beaten), Perpetrator 2 (asthma, roommate), Haruto appears
✅ Bookstore scene added (after café, deep conversation, their dynamic)
✅ Chapter 3: Tension build (Shiori's absence → dread → call)
✅ Shiori's family: Wealthy, reputation-focused, image-obsessed (explains cover-up)
✅ Chapter 5: Haruto panicking (confusion, demands answers, Shiori explains calmly)
✅ No ability names (Shiori explains HOW, not WHAT they're called)
✅ Different kill methods (drowned, crushed, burned—creative, personal)
✅ Proposal: Deep, earned, NO light dissolving
✅ Bond seal: Ring tightens, she becomes MORE solid, temperature drops, she breathes

WRITING STYLE LOCKED:
HARD-HITTING, GROUNDED, CINEMATIC

Short sentences (action)
Show don't tell (character)
Internal monologue (philosophy)
Dialogue-driven (worldview)
Visceral (violence)
Silence matters (pauses)

References: Chainsaw Man + Tokyo Ghoul + Oyasumi Punpun

