Took the evidence
Did nothing (feared scandal, image matters more)
Paid Tachibana for his silence
Tachibana refused the money (left it on their table)

He told Koyoi directly (she was 17-18 then):

Gave her copy of his findings
"Your parents won't fight for the truth. But you should know it."
Left his card: "If you ever need help."

That investigation:

Broke something in Tachibana (another injustice, no consequences)
Also: First time he saw Rift disturbance near death site (didn't understand it then)
Koyoi never called him (until much later, after her sibling's death + her own Remnant bond)


WHY HE HELPS HARUTO:
THE REASON:
Shiori's case reminded him of everything he hates:

Young victim
Wealthy perpetrators
Parents paid off
Truth buried
System failed

When Haruto came to him (after manifestation):
Haruto: "I need to find the men who killed Shiori Mizuki."
Tachibana: (recognizes name) "That was ruled suicide."
Haruto: "It wasn't. Her parents covered it up."
Tachibana: (pulls file—he'd already looked into it) "I know. I found eight names. All protected. Police won't touch it."
Haruto: "Then I will."
Tachibana: (studies him) "You know what you're asking me to help with."
Haruto: "Yes."
Tachibana: (pause, lights cigarette) "I've spent fifteen years watching guilty men walk free. I'm tired of watching."
Haruto: "Then help me stop watching."
Tachibana: "You understand—if you go after them, there's no going back. You'll be the criminal."
Haruto: "I'm already dead. I just haven't stopped moving yet."
Tachibana: (long silence, then slides folder across desk) "Locations. Routines. Weaknesses. Everything I found."
Haruto: "Why help me?"
Tachibana: "Because I'm too old and too tired to do it myself. And because someone should."

THE DEAL:
Tachibana provides:

Intelligence (locations, schedules, connections)
Cover (manipulates evidence, misleads police)
Resources (burner phones, safe houses if needed)

Haruto provides:

Justice (the kind Tachibana can't deliver legally)
Closure (for himself, and symbolically for all Tachibana's failed cases)

Tachibana's condition:

"I don't want to know how you do it. Just that it gets done."

Unspoken truth:

Tachibana knows Haruto will kill them
He's complicit
He doesn't care anymore
"Better a vigilante than nothing."


TACHIBANA'S PHILOSOPHY:
"The system is broken. It protects the powerful and abandons the powerless. I spent fifteen years trying to fix it from inside. I failed. Now I help people fix it from outside. Is it legal? No. Is it justice? Closer than what the courts offer."

CONNECTION TO KOYOI (SETUP FOR FRAGMENT 宵):
In Koyoi's fragment:

After her Remnant bond, she'll contact Tachibana again
"You told me the truth once. I need more."
He helps her track down those responsible
Recognizes she's different now (sees her eyepatch, senses danger)
"What happened to you?"
"I stopped waiting for justice."
He understands immediately

This creates parallel:

Tachibana helped both Haruto and Koyoi
Both became something beyond human
Both pursuing their own form of justice
He's the thread connecting their stories


