HOW HARUTO MEETS TACHIBANA:
THE SETUP:
After visiting Shiori's family and noticing their strange behavior, Haruto starts digging.
What he notices at the family visit:
Shiori's Mother:

Won't make eye contact
Keeps checking phone nervously
Answers in short sentences
"It was a tragedy. We're moving on. You should too." (cold, rehearsed)

Shiori's Father:

Defensive when Haruto asks questions
"The police investigated. It's closed."
Uncomfortable when Haruto mentions she seemed happy
Rushes Haruto out

What doesn't add up:

No grieving (just cold efficiency)
Furniture already being moved (too soon)
Expensive new car in driveway (when did they get that?)
Shiori's room already cleared out (her things gone)


HARUTO'S SEARCH:
He starts asking around:

Shiori's friends: "She wasn't suicidal. She was planning a trip with you."
Campus counselor: "No records of depression or crisis visits."
Her favorite bookstore owner: "She was here the day before. Bought books for your trip. She was excited."

Nothing fits the suicide narrative.
Then: Overhears the drunk confession (Day 12)

FINDING TACHIBANA:
Day 13 - Morning:
Haruto doesn't know where to go.

Can't go to police (they closed the case)
Can't confront perpetrators alone (he's just a college student)
Needs evidence, needs help

He searches online:

"Private investigator Tokyo"
"Covered up crimes"
"Sexual assault cases dismissed"

Finds article: "Former Detective Criticizes Police Corruption - Quits Force"

Article from 5 years ago
Mentions Tachibana Ryuu by name
Quoted: "When the system protects predators, good cops become complicit."

Haruto finds his office address.

THE MEETING - SCENE:
TACHIBANA'S OFFICE - AFTERNOON
Location:

Small office above ramen shop
Cheap furniture, filing cabinets overflowing
Cigarette smoke thick in air
Tachibana at desk, typing report

Door opens.
Haruto enters (no appointment).
Tachibana (doesn't look up):

"I don't take walk-ins. Make an appointment."

Haruto:

"Shiori Mizuki."

Tachibana stops typing.

Looks up
Studies Haruto (recognizes desperation)
"The suicide case. Two weeks ago."

Haruto:

"It wasn't suicide."

Tachibana (leans back, lights fresh cigarette):

"Police say it was."

Haruto:

"Police are wrong. Or lying."

Tachibana:

"What makes you think I can help?"

Haruto:

"I read about you. You quit because the system protects the guilty."
Steps forward
"I need evidence. I need to know who did this."

Tachibana (pause, exhales smoke):

"Evidence for what? Justice? Closure?"

Haruto:

"Both."

Tachibana:

"You're not asking me to take this to court."

Haruto:

"No."

Tachibana (studies him carefully):

"You want names. Locations. Proof."
"And then what?"

Haruto (doesn't flinch):

"Then I handle it."

Long silence.
Tachibana:

"Sit down."


THE CONVERSATION:
Tachibana:

"Tell me everything. From the beginning."

Haruto explains:

Shiori's death (ruled suicide)
His suspicions (family acting strange)
Her friends' statements (she wasn't depressed)
The confession he overheard (drunk perpetrator's friend)

Tachibana listens.

Takes notes
Asks pointed questions
"Her family paid off?"
"Perpetrators wealthy?"

Haruto:

"I think so. Her father mentioned 'discretion' and 'moving forward.'"

Tachibana (nods slowly):

"Classic pattern. Rich kids, poor victim, family buys silence."
Stubs out cigarette
"Give me three days. I'll get you everything."

Haruto:

"Why help me?"

Tachibana:

"Because I've seen this exact scenario fifteen times in my career."
"And every single time, the guilty walked free."
Looks directly at Haruto
"I'm tired of watching."


THE DEAL:
Tachibana:

"I find the evidence. Names, addresses, patterns."
"But I don't want to know what you do with it."
"Understood?"

Haruto:

"Understood."

Tachibana hands him card:

"Burner phone number. Use it. Don't call my office line."

Haruto leaves.
Tachibana watches him go.

Lights another cigarette
Opens laptop
Starts typing: "MIZUKI, Shiori - Confidential Investigation"


3 DAYS LATER (Day 16):
Tachibana calls Haruto:

"I have what you need. Come to the office."

Haruto arrives.
Tachibana slides folder across desk:

Photos
Names
Addresses
